Politicians allied to the Jubilee party and Deputy President William Ruto’s United Democratic Alliance (UDA) are preparing for a showdown as the Rurii Ward by-election . 
The mini poll, whose date is yet to be set, will have local and national implications, including at the Nyandarua county assembly, where at least nine of the MCAs who opposed the ouster of Speaker Wahome Ndegwa are allied to the DP camp. 



