Others on the UDA side are Ol Kalou MP David Kiaraho, with the legislator expected to use his position to influence voters to the DP's side. 





Rurii Ward MCA Mburu Githinji died in Nairobi after more than three years of illness.
Photo credit: Courtesy


During the funeral of the late MCA Mburu Githinji, Mr Kiaraho said he was committed to ensuring that all development projects initiated by him are completed. 
“He was very concerned about electrification, a project we have started implementing with Kenya Power in honour of the late MCA,” said Mr Kiaraho. 
The UDA section claims that the seat belongs to them and that Mr Githinji was a member of the Hustler Movement. 
But Nyandarua Majority Leader, King’ori Wambugu, dismisses this, saying the late MCA was a Jubilee loyalist and was among those that signed the impeachment motion against Speaker Ndegwa. 



